net.java.jddac.common.type
Class Float64

java.lang.Object
  net.java.jddac.common.type.Float64
Direct Known Subclasses:
Float64J2me, Float64J2se
public abstract class Float64
extends java.lang.Object

The Float64 class represents a 64 bit floating point number. Since floating point is not available on a number of platforms this class acts as an abstract interface for concrete implementations for J2SE and J2ME. When an instance is created an attempt is made to create an instance of Float64J2se. Failing that, it will create an instance of Float64J2me.
